@startuml
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #E8F4F8
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor #FFE6CC

title SD-08 - Admin Dashboard Flow

actor Administrator
participant Browser
participant Server
participant Router
participant Controller
participant Model
database Database

Administrator -> Browser: 1. Navigate to admin dashboard\nGET /administrator/home
activate Browser

Browser -> Server: 2. GET /administrator/home
activate Server
deactivate Browser

Server -> Router: 3. Route to Administrator controller home()
activate Router
deactivate Server

Router -> Controller: 4. Call home() method
activate Controller
deactivate Router

note right of Controller
    Check admin session:
    - Verify user is logged in
    - Load user permissions/modules
end note

Controller -> Model: 5. view_where('users',['username'=>$session_username])
activate Model

Model -> Database: 6. SELECT * FROM users\nWHERE username = '$session_username'
activate Database
deactivate Model

Database --> Model: 7. Return user data
deactivate Database
activate Model

Model --> Controller: 8. Return user data
deactivate Model
activate Controller

note right of Controller
    Load dashboard statistics:
    - Count total news articles
    - Count total agenda items
    - Count total albums
    - Count total users
    - Count total pages
end note

Controller -> Model: 9. view('berita')->num_rows()
activate Model

Model -> Database: 10. SELECT COUNT(*) FROM berita
activate Database
deactivate Model

Database --> Model: 11. Return news count
deactivate Database
activate Model

Model --> Controller: 12. Return news count
deactivate Model
activate Controller

Controller -> Model: 13. view('agenda')->num_rows()
activate Model

Model -> Database: 14. SELECT COUNT(*) FROM agenda
activate Database
deactivate Model

Database --> Model: 15. Return agenda count
deactivate Database
activate Model

Model --> Controller: 16. Return agenda count
deactivate Model
activate Controller

Controller -> Model: 17. view('album')->num_rows()
activate Model

Model -> Database: 18. SELECT COUNT(*) FROM album
activate Database
deactivate Model

Database --> Model: 19. Return album count
deactivate Database
activate Model

Model --> Controller: 20. Return album count
deactivate Model
activate Controller

Controller -> Model: 21. view('users')->num_rows()
activate Model

Model -> Database: 22. SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users
activate Database
deactivate Model

Database --> Model: 23. Return users count
deactivate Database
activate Model

Model --> Controller: 24. Return users count
deactivate Model
activate Controller

Controller -> Model: 25. view('halamanstatis')->num_rows()
activate Model

Model -> Database: 26. SELECT COUNT(*) FROM halamanstatis
activate Database
deactivate Model

Database --> Model: 27. Return pages count
deactivate Database
activate Model

Model --> Controller: 28. Return pages count
deactivate Model
activate Controller

note right of Controller
    Load recent activities:
    - Latest 5 news articles
    - Latest 5 agenda items
    - Recent user activities
end note

Controller -> Model: 29. view_join_ordering_limit('berita','users','username','id_berita','DESC',0,5)
activate Model

Model -> Database: 30. SELECT berita.*, users.username\nFROM berita\nJOIN users ON berita.username = users.username\nORDER BY berita.id_berita DESC LIMIT 5
activate Database
deactivate Model

Database --> Model: 31. Return recent news
deactivate Database
activate Model

Model --> Controller: 32. Return recent news
deactivate Model
activate Controller

Controller -> Model: 33. view_join_ordering_limit('agenda','users','username','id_agenda','DESC',0,5)
activate Model

Model -> Database: 34. SELECT agenda.*, users.username\nFROM agenda\nJOIN users ON agenda.username = users.username\nORDER BY agenda.id_agenda DESC LIMIT 5
activate Database
deactivate Model

Database --> Model: 35. Return recent agenda
deactivate Database
activate Model

Model --> Controller: 36. Return recent agenda
deactivate Model
activate Controller

note right of Controller
    Prepare dashboard data:
    - Statistics counts
    - Recent activities
    - User permissions
    - System status
end note

Controller -> Browser: 37. Render dashboard template\n(template().'/administrator/home', $data)
activate Browser

Browser -> Administrator: 38. Display admin dashboard\nwith statistics and recent activities
deactivate Browser

opt Administrator clicks menu items
    Administrator -> Browser: 39. Click menu link\nGET /administrator/menu_action
    activate Browser

    Browser -> Server: 40. GET /administrator/menu_action
    activate Server
    deactivate Browser

    Server -> Router: 41. Route to Administrator controller menu_action()
    activate Router
    deactivate Server

    Router -> Controller: 42. Call menu_action() method
    activate Controller
    deactivate Router

    note right of Controller
        Handle menu actions:
        - News management
        - Agenda management
        - User management
        - Content management
        - System configuration
    end note

    Controller -> Browser: 43. Render appropriate admin template
    activate Browser

    Browser -> Administrator: 44. Display admin management page
    deactivate Browser
end

@enduml
